<dl id="n03020b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n03" href="#n03020b">N03 (VI.B.3)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n03all.htm#n03020b"> 20(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> S Patrick&apos;s vision / 1 All I ablaze ~ <small>Orange</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n03020b"><li>FW 21.16 </li><li><a href="../../flex/a/lexa.htm#n03020b">2010</a> </li><li><a href="../../flex/a/l39a.htm#n03020b">1939</a> </li><li><ms href="#n03020b">MS BL 47472-25</ms> </li><li>JJA 44:128 <a name="ad2" href="../../ff/fdra/ada.htm#ad2">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/a/ad2.htm#n03020b">Draft: I.1&sect;2.2</a></li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources">The writer of <font color="green">[an ancient Irish]</font> manuscript says that &ldquo;the First Order <font color="green">[of Irish saints]</font> was most holy, the Second Order holier, and the Third holy. The First glowed like the sun in the fervour of their charity; the Second cast a pale radiance like the moon; the Third shone like the aurora. These Three Orders the blessed Patrick foreknew, enlightened by heavenly wisdom, when in prophetic vision <mark>he saw at first all Ireland ablaze</mark>, and afterwards only the mountains on fire; and at last saw lamps lit in the valleys.&rdquo; <small> J.M. Flood, <a name="JMFI" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#JMFI"><cite title="source">Ireland: Its Saints and Scholars</cite></a> (n.d) 43-4</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: See also: <a name="n12104i" href="n12all.htm#n12104i">N12 (VI.B.14):104(i)</a> </mm> </dd></dl>
